  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the Quality of Basic Education in Northern Ghana</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Although the rate of school enrolment is increasing in Ghana, the quality of education children receive can be poor, especially in the poorer north of the country. In one northern district, for example, the number of children passing the Basic Education Certificate fell from 9% to 6.5% over 2009-2011. Many children go into school with no English, and struggle learning from teachers with no training who mostly teach by rote. This project will improve the quality of teaching by encouraging the use of mother tongue in early grades and encouraging teachers to focus on the child and be more aware of the girls in their classrooms. It will also provide appropriate teaching materials, and on-going training and supervision for teachers. More than 40 000 children in grades 1-3 will have significantly improved literacy by the end of the project.</narrative>
  </description>
